Project-2 Installation Instructions
===================================

Overview
--------
This project performs GPU-based image retrieval on the sklearn digits dataset
using PyTorch CUDA tensor operations.

Linux / Kaggle (Recommended for final proof)
-------------------------------------------
1) Ensure Python 3.10+ is available.
2) Install dependencies:
   pip install -r requirements.txt
3) Run:
   python3 src/run_retrieval_gpu.py --output-dir proof --max-images 1797 --query-count 300 --top-k 5 --batch-size 128 --seed 42

Local Debug (No GPU)
--------------------
You may run CPU-only for debugging:
   python3 src/run_retrieval_gpu.py --allow-cpu --output-dir proof

Important
---------
CPU debugging runs are not valid as final assignment proof.
Final proof artifacts should be produced in a GPU-enabled environment.
